Given a input sentence (your paper's title), this code generates all possible abbreviate words,
whose characters are all from the given sentence.

This code use NLTK to do the input sentence pre-processing, therefore, you may need to install NLTK at first.
Use the following command to install nltk, and download the required word dictionary.

# pip install nltk
# python -c "nltk.download('words');nltk.download('averaged_perceptron_tagger')"

Using this code is simple:
# python main.py --title "Generate Fantastic Title by Using a Single Line Command" --word_len 5 --mnc 1 --num_threads 10 --constraint 'mcow'
